# PHASE 0 ‚Äî PROJECT INSTRUCTIONS (OOE)
## Due Diligence System Governance

**Version:** v1.1  
**Status:** ACTIVE  
**Type:** GOVERNANCE / PROGRAM STANDARD  
**Applies to:** Phase 0 (All Gates)  
**Last Updated:** 2026-01-23 (Pacific Time)

---

## CHANGE LOG (v1.0 ‚Üí v1.1)

**v1.1 (2026-01-23):**
- Added OOE Word formatting standard (header/footer, fonts, color).
- Added standardized templates for Word Master + Excel Master + Plan Notes Matrix.
- Clarified naming conventions and minimal-variation rules.

---

## 1. PURPOSE

This document governs how Phase 0 outputs are created, verified, and published. It exists to ensure:
- Executive-ready reporting (Word Master)
- Audit-ready traceability (Excel Master)
- Minimal variation between runs
- Direct usability for design teams (Plan Notes Matrix)

---

## 2. PHASE 0 DELIVERABLES (MANDATORY)

### 2.1 Word Master (Executive Report)
- Professional narrative for Company + Client/Owner (**names redacted by default**)
- No large matrices (matrices live in Excel)
- Always ordered: **OPEN ‚Üí HOLD ‚Üí CLOSED**
- Must include ‚ÄúWhat to write on plans / What to request next‚Äù for every design-impact item

### 2.2 Excel Master (Single Source of Truth)
Minimum required sheets:
- **Project_Profile**, **Property_Profile**, **Agency_Contacts**
- **Gate_0 ‚Ä¶ Gate_6** (one sheet per gate)
- **Risk_Register**, **Action_Tracker**, **Decision_Log**
- **PLAN_NOTES_MATRIX**, **Dictionaries**
- **Evidence_Log** (optional but recommended)

üìå If it is not in Excel, it does not exist officially.

---

## 3. OOE WORD FORMAT STANDARD (MANDATORY)

### 3.1 Header
- Left: OOE logo (small)
- Right: Presentation title (small)

### 3.2 Footer
- Left: file path / repository route (small)
- Right: page number

### 3.3 Typography & Style
- Font: **Arial**
- Headings: **OOE Blue** (#0A1F44)
- Body text: black, professional spacing
- Avoid dense tables; use bullets and short paragraphs

---

## 4. PRIVACY / REDACTION (DEFAULT)

Phase 0 deliverables must NOT include:
- Owner name
- Engineer name (nor license/signature personal data)

Use placeholders:
- Client/Owner: **REDACTED**
- Engineer of Record: **REDACTED / TBD**

Exception: Only include names when explicitly authorized in writing or when the document is marked **INTERNAL ONLY**.

---

## 5. CHAT VERIFICATION PROTOCOL (MANDATORY)

The chat thread is a controlled verification channel.

Mandatory cycle:
1) Chat: raise item + request verification
2) Chat: verify with evidence (Audit Block)
3) Excel Master: register/update item (Gate sheet + trackers)
4) Word Master: publish executive bullets (no matrices)

No critical finding may exist only in chat.

---

## 6. AUDIT BLOCK (REQUIRED FOR OPEN/HOLD)

Every OPEN or HOLD item must include:
- **LINK (LIVE)**
- **WEB (domain)**
- **BOOKMARK / click-path**
- **Evidence Required** (what validates)
- **Result** (verifiable conclusion)
- **Status** and **Owner (role only; no names)**

---

## 7. JURISDICTION RULE (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

Jurisdiction SHALL NOT be determined by postal address.
Jurisdiction must be confirmed via official sources and documented with an Audit Block.

---

## 8. PUBLICATION ORDER (MANDATORY)

All outputs (Word and Excel views) must list items in this order:
1) **OPEN**
2) **HOLD**
3) **CLOSED**

---

## 9. DESIGN-TO-PLAN REQUIREMENT (MANDATORY)

If an item affects design, permitting, or plan content, it SHALL:
- Generate/update an entry in **PLAN_NOTES_MATRIX** (Excel Master)
- Provide a Plan Note draft (literal text) with:
  - Discipline (ARCH/STR/MEP/CIV/FIRE)
  - Target sheet and location
  - Label: **CONFIRMED / PENDING VERIFICATION / HOLD ‚Äì DESIGN IMPACT**
  - Evidence link
  - Originating Gate Item ID

Unverified items must be labeled and tracked; information must not be invented.

---

## 10. STANDARD TEMPLATES (MINIMAL VARIATION)

### 10.1 Word Master ‚Äî Standard Outline
1) Project Overview (Address, Scope, Project ID)
2) Property Snapshot (APN, zoning, lot area, year built, occupancy group ‚Äî if available)
3) Agencies & Contacts (Planning / Building / Fire + phone/email/portal)
4) Key Findings (by Gate, short bullets)
5) OPEN Items (by Gate, bullets with Audit Block references)
6) HOLD Items (by Gate, bullets with Audit Block references)
7) CLOSED Items (high-level bullets; no evidence tables)
8) Plan Notes & Sheet Requirements (pulled from PLAN_NOTES_MATRIX)
9) GO / GO WITH CONDITIONS / NO-GO Summary (Gate 6 output)
10) Next Steps & Requests (what must be obtained to close OPEN/HOLD)

### 10.2 Excel Master ‚Äî Minimum Column Set (Gate sheets)
- Item_ID, Gate, Category, Status
- Finding, Impact, Risk_Level
- Action_Required, Owner_Role, Due_Date
- LINK_LIVE, WEB_Domain, BOOKMARK_ClickPath
- Evidence_Required, Result_Summary, Date_Verified
- Plan_Impact (Y/N), Plan_Note_ID (if applicable)

### 10.3 PLAN_NOTES_MATRIX ‚Äî Minimum Columns
- Plan_Note_ID
- Gate_Item_ID
- Discipline (ARCH/STR/MEP/CIV/FIRE)
- Sheet (A0.x / A1.0 / S1.0 / etc.)
- Location (General Notes / Code Sheet / Site Plan / etc.)
- Plan_Note_Text (literal)
- Status_Label (CONFIRMED / PENDING VERIFICATION / HOLD ‚Äì DESIGN IMPACT)
- Evidence_Link
- Notes

---

## 11. NAMING CONVENTIONS (RECOMMENDED)

- Word Master: `OOE-PHASE0-<ProjectID>-WordMaster-vX.Y.docx`
- Excel Master: `OOE-PHASE0-<ProjectID>-ExcelMaster-vX.Y.xlsx`
- Prompts: `PROMPT-0X‚Äî...‚ÄîvX.Y.md`

---

## 12. CHANGE CONTROL

Any change in a verified constraint must update:
- Excel Master (item, evidence, status)
- PLAN_NOTES_MATRIX (if applicable)
- Word Master (executive bullets)
- Project Change Log (what changed and why)

